{
  "stem": "25773.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was-- I went to school, you know?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Went to, first, the school which all the Polish children went compulsory till seven.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I went to a Jewish gymnasium called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I loved the school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I met nice friends, lovely friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I enjoyed learning.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that was-- I finished in '38.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was yet not quite certain what I would do.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Probably would-- having the opportunity, maybe I would have studied, probably would, some kind of-- because I liked learning.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And there was the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were, we were, we were absolutely-- [? and ?] although, we lived for 16, 17 years in the Warsaw, in Warsaw in the part which was not predominately Jewish at all, we were absolutely acknowledged Jews.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father returned regularly to synagogue.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, we went--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a local synagogue, near our place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Occasionally, on very big occasions, we went to the [NON-ENGLISH] synagogue, which was one of the greatest-- really beautiful, which was unfortunately burned down.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my two brothers, who went to gymnasium, and my other brother, actually, stepbrother, actually finished gymnasium very successfully and went to studies.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the little one who was still small, we were regularly to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were also Zionist-orientated, though Palestine, at that time, was very remote, this place.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we were remotely associated because of my father's uncle, was Nahum Sokolow.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nahum Sokolow.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nahum Sokolow.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- it was not-- my grandmother and Nahum Sokolow's wife were sisters.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was not a very close association, but I didn't meet him ever.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My sister did, I think.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
